org.knime.core.node.workflow

Class FlowScopeContext

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.knime.core.node.workflow.FlowObject
      • org.knime.core.node.workflow.FlowScopeContext
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Cloneable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    FlowLoopContext, FlowSubnodeScopeContext, FlowTryCatchContext

    public class FlowScopeContext
extends FlowObject
    Control object on a FlowObjectStack to indicate presence of a scope. The object is used to remove all content from the stack when the scope is left. More complex derived classes represent loops and try-catch-constructs.
    Since:
    2.8
    Author:
    M. Berthold, KNIME.com, Zurich, Switzerland
    No public API: not to be extended by clients
    This class is not intended to be subclassed by clients.
